PART 4: BETTI NUMBERS OF Ind(G) FOR CONFLICT GRAPHS
======================================================================

Conflict graph properties would require cycle enumeration (expensive).
Instead, let's compute Betti numbers of Ind(G) for small named graphs:

  K_3 (triangle) (n=3):
    f-vector: [1, 3]
    I(G, 2) = 7
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = -2

  P_4 (path) (n=4):
    f-vector: [1, 4, 3]
    I(G, 2) = 21
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = 0

  C_4 (4-cycle) (n=4):
    f-vector: [1, 4, 2]
    I(G, 2) = 17
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = -1

  C_5 (5-cycle) (n=5):
    f-vector: [1, 5, 5]
    I(G, 2) = 31
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = 1

  K_4 (complete) (n=4):
    f-vector: [1, 4]
    I(G, 2) = 9
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = -3

  K_{2,3} (n=5):
    f-vector: [1, 5, 4, 1]
    I(G, 2) = 35
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = -1

  Empty_4 (n=4):
    f-vector: [1, 4, 6, 4, 1]
    I(G, 2) = 81
    I(G, -1) = χ(Ind) = 0

======================================================================
PART 5: THE OPERAD — COMPOSING INDEPENDENCE POLYNOMIALS
======================================================================

The deletion-contraction identity creates an OPERAD structure:

  I(G) = I(G-v) + x · I(G-N[v])

This says: to compute I(G), choose a vertex v, then:
  - Delete v: contributes I(G-v) (configurations not using v)
  - Delete N[v]: contributes x·I(G-N[v]) (configurations using v)

This is a TREE DECOMPOSITION: each graph decomposes into a binary tree
of smaller graphs. The leaves are:
  - Empty graph: I(∅) = 1
  - Single vertex: I(K_1) = 1 + x

The OPERAD COMPOSITION: If G has components G_1, ..., G_k:
  I(G) = I(G_1) × ... × I(G_k)

This product structure makes {I(G)} an ALGEBRA over the operad of
graph decompositions.

For tournaments: H(T) = I(Ω(T), 2) inherits this operad structure.
The OCF is the "composition series" of the conflict graph Ω(T).

Deletion-contraction tree for P_4 at x=2:
  I(P_4) = I(P_4 - v_0) + 2·I(P_4 - N[v_0])
         = I(P_3) + 2·I(P_2)
         = (I(P_2) + 2·I(P_1)) + 2·I(P_2)
         = 3·I(P_2) + 2·I(P_1)
         = 3·(I(P_1) + 2·I(P_0)) + 2·I(P_1)
         = 5·I(P_1) + 6·I(P_0)
         = 5·(1+2) + 6·1 = 15 + 6 = 21
  Verify: I(P_4, 2) = 21

DC tree coefficients: I(P_k, 2) = a_k × 3 + b_k × 1
  k=2: a=    1, b=    2, 3a+b=       5, actual=       5, match=True
  k=3: a=    3, b=    2, 3a+b=      11, actual=      11, match=True
  k=4: a=    5, b=    6, 3a+b=      21, actual=      21, match=True
  k=5: a=   11, b=   10, 3a+b=      43, actual=      43, match=True
  k=6: a=   21, b=   22, 3a+b=      85, actual=      85, match=True
  k=7: a=   43, b=   42, 3a+b=     171, actual=     171, match=True
  k=8: a=   85, b=   86, 3a+b=     341, actual=     341, match=True
  k=9: a=  171, b=  170, 3a+b=     683, actual=     683, match=True

